    "asOf": "2020-10-16",
    "date": "2021-03-18T16:49:10Z",
    "text": "Policing Transparency Act\n\nThis bill requires states and local governments, in order to receive certain federal funds, to (1) report annually to the National Use-of-Force Data Collection of the Federal Bureau of Investigation on use-of-force events by law enforcement officers resulting in fatalities, serious bodily injuries, and firearm discharges; and (2) maintain a system for sharing disciplinary records of law enforcement officers.\n\nThe bill also requires the Department of Justice to award a one-time grant to each state for establishing the systems for sharing disciplinary records."
  },
